SIMPLE: predatory
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predatory
<hw>Pred"a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praedatorius</ets>, fr. <ets>praedari</ets> to plunder, fr.
<ets>praeda</ets> prey. See <er>Prey</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Characterized by plundering; practicing rapine; plundering;
pillaging; <as>as, a <ex>predatory</ex> excursion; a <ex>predatory</ex>
party.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>predatory</xex> war.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hungry; ravenous; <as>as, <ex>predatory</ex>
spirits</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Exercise . . . maketh the spirits more hot and
<qex>predatory</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Living by preying upon other
animals; carnivorous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prede</ent>⟦br⟧
